Sumitomo Mitsui Asset Management Company LTD Raised Electronic Arts (EA) Holding By $8.42 Million, Party City Has 1.44 Sentiment


					
						July 27, 2017 - By Adrian Mccoy

Sumitomo Mitsui Asset Management Company Ltd increased Electronic Arts Inc (EA) stake by 297.39% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Sumitomo Mitsui Asset Management Company Ltd acquired 108,008 shares as Electronic Arts Inc (EA)’s stock rose 23.30%. The Sumitomo Mitsui Asset Management Company Ltd holds 144,327 shares with $11.37 million value, up from 36,319 last quarter. Electronic Arts Inc now has $36.50B valuation. The stock increased 3.82% or $4.34 during the last trading session, reaching $118. About 477 shares traded. Electronic Arts Inc. (NASDAQ:EA) has risen 46.45% since July 27, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 29.75% the S&P500.







Paylocity Holding Corporation is a cloud well-known provider of payroll and human capital management , software solutions for medium-sized organizations. The company has market cap of $2.45 billion. The Company’s services are provided in a software-as-a-service delivery model utilizing its cloud platform. It has a 561.4 P/E ratio. The cloud platform provides a suite of applications using a multi-tenant architecture.
Shearlink Capital Llc holds 4.18% of its portfolio in Paylocity Holding Corp for 414,042 shares. Weatherbie Capital Llc owns 717,280 shares or 2.7% of their US portfolio. Moreover, Echo Street Capital Management Llc has 0.58% invested in the company for 484,419 shares. The Minnesota-based Riverbridge Partners Llc has invested 0.56% in the stock. Segantii Capital Management Ltd, a Hong Kong-based fund reported 50,000 shares.
Ratings analysis reveals 50% of Paylocity’s analysts are positive. Out of 6 Wall Street analysts rating Paylocity, 3 give it “Buy”, 0 “Sell” rating, while 3 recommend “Hold”. The lowest target is $40.0 while the high is $50.0. The stock’s average target of $46 is -4.09% below today’s ($47.96) share price. PCTY was included in 6 notes of analysts from September 20, 2016. On Tuesday, September 20 the stock rating was initiated by Pacific Crest with “Sector Weight”. First Analysis upgraded it to “Overweight” rating and $48.0 target in Friday, November 4 report. RBC Capital Markets initiated Paylocity Holding Corp (NASDAQ:PCTY) on Friday, September 30 with “Sector Perform” rating. The firm has “Buy” rating by Bank of America given on Friday, February 3. The firm earned “Perform” rating on Friday, December 2 by Oppenheimer. As per Friday, February 3, the company rating was maintained by Needham.
The stock decreased 0.08% or $0.04 during the last trading session, reaching $47.96. About shares traded. Paylocity Holding Corp (PCTY) has risen 26.16% since July 27, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 9.46% the S&P500.
Analysts await Paylocity Holding Corp (NASDAQ:PCTY) to report earnings on August, 8. They expect $-0.10 EPS, 0.00% or $0.00 from last year’s $-0.1 per share. After $0.28 actual EPS reported by Paylocity Holding Corp for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts -135.71% negative EPS growth. 
Since February 1, 2017, it had 0 insider buys, and 43 selling transactions for $60.36 million activity. The insider Soderlund Patrick sold $5.57 million. On Tuesday, May 23 the insider HOAG JAY C sold $754,375. Another trade for 10,000 shares valued at $893,151 was made by MOORE PETER R. on Monday, April 3. On Tuesday, May 23 the insider Miele Laura sold $275,000. Shares for $914,585 were sold by Wilson Andrew on Thursday, June 1. The insider LINZNER JOEL sold $425,000. Jorgensen Blake J sold $1.08 million worth of stock.
Among 20 analysts covering Electronic Arts (NASDAQ:EA), 19 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 1 Hold. Therefore 95% are positive. Electronic Arts had 45 analyst reports since July 28, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The rating was maintained by Stifel Nicolaus on Monday, October 17 with “Buy”. On Friday, May 26 the stock rating was maintained by Credit Suisse with “Buy”. The stock of Electronic Arts Inc. (NASDAQ:EA) earned “Outperform” rating by Credit Suisse on Monday, January 25. Piper Jaffray maintained the shares of EA in report on Friday, June 23 with “Buy” rating. BMO Capital Markets maintained the shares of EA in report on Monday, June 12 with “Hold” rating. Morgan Stanley initiated Electronic Arts Inc. (NASDAQ:EA) on Friday, September 23 with “Overweight” rating. The firm has “Buy” rating given on Monday, July 17 by Jefferies. As per Monday, August 10, the company rating was maintained by Piper Jaffray. Atlantic Securities upgraded Electronic Arts Inc. (NASDAQ:EA) on Friday, December 4 to “Overweight” rating. Mizuho maintained Electronic Arts Inc. (NASDAQ:EA) on Friday, October 30 with “Buy” rating.
Investors sentiment increased to 0.85 in Q4 2016. Its up 0.04, from 0.81 in 2016Q3. It increased, as 71 investors sold EA shares while 214 reduced holdings. 65 funds opened positions while 178 raised stakes. 290.67 million shares or 1.29% less from 294.46 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Aviva Public Limited Co has 188,259 shares for 0.09% of their portfolio. Ahl Prtn Limited Liability Partnership holds 0.04% or 15,977 shares. State Of Wisconsin Board has invested 0.09% in Electronic Arts Inc. (NASDAQ:EA). Whittier Trust Of Nevada Inc invested 0.01% in Electronic Arts Inc. (NASDAQ:EA). Barclays Public Lc holds 0.03% of its portfolio in Electronic Arts Inc. (NASDAQ:EA) for 316,861 shares. Moreover, Agf has 0% invested in Electronic Arts Inc. (NASDAQ:EA). Whittier holds 0.01% or 2,386 shares in its portfolio. Fiduciary Trust accumulated 9,976 shares or 0.03% of the stock. Moreover, Schwab Charles Inv has 0.07% invested in Electronic Arts Inc. (NASDAQ:EA) for 868,660 shares. Moreover, Marsico Cap Mgmt has 0.15% invested in Electronic Arts Inc. (NASDAQ:EA) for 44,171 shares. Cim Ltd Liability has 4,900 shares for 0.19% of their portfolio. Herndon holds 384 shares or 0% of its portfolio. Wetherby Asset Mngmt invested in 0.09% or 6,083 shares. Ubs Asset Americas Incorporated stated it has 0.14% in Electronic Arts Inc. (NASDAQ:EA). Voloridge Management Lc stated it has 99,437 shares or 0.17% of all its holdings.
Sumitomo Mitsui Asset Management Company Ltd decreased Cme Group Inc (NASDAQ:CME) stake by 4,258 shares to 53,832 valued at $6.21M in 2016Q4. It also reduced United Technologies Corp (NYSE:UTX) stake by 3,915 shares and now owns 73,802 shares. Wells Fargo & Co New (NYSE:WFC) was reduced too. 








